{
  "texts": [
    "For 1, we prove up-R and R-down at the same time.",
    "Supposex ′ ⊑ x, y ′ ⊑ y and x ′ R □ i y.",
    "To show that xR □ i y ′, consider any Z ∈ P with x ∈ ■ F i Z.",
    "Then since F is a partial-state frame, ■ F i Z ∈ P, so ■ F i Z satisfies persistence by the assumption of part 1, so from x ′ ⊑ x and x ∈ ■ F i Z we have x ′ ∈ ■ F i Z.",
    "Then since x ′ R □i y, we have y ∈ Z, which with y ′ ⊑ y and persistence for Z implies y ′ ∈ Z."
  ]
}